## Step 3 — Sort Your Existing Files

This is the big one. Look through your local machine for {{DOMAIN}}-related files and sort them into the right folders. Here's a guide for common file types:

### Where does this file go?

| File Type | Folder | Examples |
|-----------|--------|----------|
| {{WORKFLOW_TOOL}} workflow exports | `Workflows/Exports/` | `workflow-name_v3.json` |
| Connection/credential docs | `Workflows/Configs/` | `service-connection-config.md` |
| Workflow review notes | `Workflows/Reviews/` | `workflow-review.md` |
| Hardware/network docs | `Docs/` | Server configs, IP tables, switch configs |
| Migration plans, roadmaps | `Planning/` | Timeline docs, questionnaires |
| How-to procedures, SOPs | `Knowledge/Procedures/` | "How to restore a backup" |
| Client environment notes | `Knowledge/Client-Notes/` | "ACME Corp — server inventory" |
| Vendor reference info | `Knowledge/Vendor-Notes/` | "Vendor compatibility notes" |
| Change records | `Operations/Change-Log/` | "2026-03-10 — Replaced firewall" |
| Incident notes | `Operations/Incidents/` | "2026-03-05 — VPN outage" |
| Scheduled maintenance | `Operations/Maintenance/` | "Q1 2026 patch schedule" |
| AI-generated analysis | `Reviews/` | System reviews, audit reports |
| Reports for leadership | `Outputs/` | Performance reports, SLA summaries |
| Old files, superseded docs | `Archive/` | Anything that's been replaced |

### Sorting Process

Work through this one category at a time. For each category:

1. Search your machine for related files (Desktop, Documents, Downloads, etc.)
2. Copy them into the correct {{REPO_NAME}} folder
3. Rename if needed — use descriptive names with dates: `YYYY-MM-DD_Description.md`
4. Check off the category below

**Categories to sort through:**

- [ ] **{{WORKFLOW_TOOL}} Workflows** — Export your important workflows and save them to `Workflows/Exports/`
- [ ] **Infrastructure Docs** — Hardware specs, network diagrams, switch configs → `Docs/`
- [ ] **Procedures & SOPs** — Any "how I do X" notes → `Knowledge/Procedures/`
- [ ] **Client Notes** — Per-client technical knowledge (sanitized) → `Knowledge/Client-Notes/`
- [ ] **Vendor Notes** — Vendor-specific reference info → `Knowledge/Vendor-Notes/`
- [ ] **Planning Docs** — Active plans, timelines, proposals → `Planning/`
- [ ] **Old/Superseded Files** — Anything not actively used → `Archive/`

> **Tip:** Don't try to sort everything in one sitting. Start with the most important stuff and add more over time.

