## Step 5 — Your First Commit

Once you've sorted some files in, commit them:

```bash
cd ~/path/to/{{REPO_DIR}}

# See what's changed
git status

# Stage everything
git add -A

# Commit with a descriptive message
git commit -m "Organize files: add workflows, procedures, and notes"

# Push to GitHub
git push origin main
```

- [ ] I've made my first commit and pushed

