## Step 7 — Let AI Help You

You have powerful AI tools configured. Here's how to use them to stay organized:

| Task | How to Ask Claude |
|------|-------------------|
| Write a procedure from memory | "Write a step-by-step procedure for [task]. I'll review and correct it." |
| Summarize an incident | "Summarize this incident as a report. Include timeline, root cause, and resolution." |
| Review a workflow | "Review this workflow. What could be improved?" |
| Draft a change log entry | "Draft a change log entry for: [what changed] on [date]" |

### What Needs Your Input vs What AI Can Handle

| **AI Can Handle** | **You Need to Provide** |
|-------------------|------------------------|
| Draft procedures from your description | Verify technical accuracy |
| Format and organize notes | The actual knowledge/content |
| Write commit messages | Approve before pushing |
| Suggest file names and locations | Final decision |

- [ ] I know how to use AI tools for documentation

